reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was originally scared when I opened the package that there was only the rabbit paper, but then once I opened the individual packages I saw that the rest of the paper styles were behind the rabbits. Overall the paper is amazing and easy to write on. They are a good black color and the gold is very vibrant. The thickness is decent and does not let the ink bleed through. I used extra thin gold paint pens and the ink did not smear once it had a couple of seconds to try. I used them as invitations to a murder mystery party and thought they easily fit the aesthetic I was trying to fit.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 8, 2022
reviews.reviewText: Absolutely beautiful. Used this to write a UV reactive letter to a friend. Turns out it works perfectly even though the letter was delayed about a month before being received. The ink disappears into the black page without any issue after it dries. You temporarily have about a minute to see everything before then as it dries. Would highly recommend. Great quality.
